scenes.label: *start
texts: Yo, Pollon and Cross. This is Tabuchi Motors.
Oh? How are the graper repairs coming along?
Gonna be finished up sometime today.
Thanks. Put the payment on my tab, as always.
No can do. Not this time.
Huh? Seriously? But it was never a problem before.
It involves part replacement, and that ain't cheap. Gonna need payment up-front.
And pay your tab too, while you're at it.
Way to kick me when I'm down!
The only reason you got away with it for so long is 'cause Dub's a nice guy. You're in no position to complain.
I mean, you're not wrong, but man...
All the past repair bills, plus this one? Sounds like a lot.

scenes.label: *load
texts: Shit, I don't have that kind of cash...
I could hand over my whole fee from that recent job and it still wouldn't cover it.
Hey, Dub, weren't we buddies? What's gotten into you?
Yeah, right. You're close enough to elope.
Anyway, I'm not repairing a thing till you pay up, and that's final.
Come on, man, be a pal.
I'll consider putting it on your tab... if you hook me up with a girl.
L-like I can just find one...
Well, I'm not touchin' your graper, then. Later.
Goddammit! Why'd he have to be like that?! Screw him! Our friendship was over!
This is gonna affect our work as Nakano Symphonies...
...Fine, I'll handle the payment this time.
I'm sure some of the people I know will let me borrow money.
Got no choice. You're gonna be working without pay for a while.
That was a pretty harsh condition, but...

Whoa! Italy! Ciao ciao! Al denteee!

texts: Hey, Cross, you got any unpaid tabs from graper maintenance and stuff?
I don't abuse mine like you do, so for me, upkeep isn't that expensive. I pay in full every time.
Really? That's a shame. If you had any unpaid tabs, I was gonna pay 'em for ya.
Good timing, I was just about to call you.
Gonna be finished up sometime today.
But I can't put it on your tab. It involves part replacement, and that ain't cheap.
And pay your tab too, while you're at it.
All the past repair bills, plus this one...? Shit, that's gonna be a lot.
Sure thing. I'll pay right away.
Hell yeah I do. And lots of it.
Your boy just won the MiniLotto.
...Stop lying or I won't fix your graper.
This is the number I bought, and this is the winner.

texts: Wh-what the hell's— I mean, h-how did you...?!
I don't think I'd even seen Cross like this before.
Heh. So yeah, Dub. I'm pretty rich right now. I'll pay for the repairs and the tab, so fix my ride, will ya?
You... First you get a gf...and now you're rich... Lucky bastard...
Sorry, Pollon. I don't think I can fix your graper, ever again...
You just made me realize I'm never gonna amount to anything.
I'm gonna go sulk in bed.
I know you're happy about that money, but sometimes you really let things go to your head. It's a bad habit of yours.

texts: This money's gonna go towards funding Nakano Symphonies.
Also, we're about to get a call from Dub about the graper repairs. And, uh, I want you to use these funds to cover the repairs for me.
Yo, Pollon and Cross. This is Tabuchi Motors.
How are the graper repairs coming along?
Gonna be finished up sometime today.
But I can't put it on your tab. It involves part replacement, and that ain't cheap.
And pay your tab too, while you're at it.
Yep, there it was. I looked Cross in the eyes. This was the signal.
Hm? Really? You got the money?
I guess I can trust you on that. I'll keep working on it.
Phew... That went well. A perfect recovery.
I got the money, Dub was gonna fix my graper, and we could stay friends.
Hey... Did you use that Saving and Loading thing?
Yeah. Nothing's off the table for your boy now.
I dunno... I wouldn't let it go to your head, if I were you.
I knew exactly what he meant—he was wary of this function.
Realistically, an app this insane shouldn't even exist.
Even to me it felt like some kind of illusion, and I was the one using it.
It was crazy how useful it was. How the hell did it even work?
